The paper deals with compressed sensing of sparse rank-one matrices, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed algorithm also involves matrix factorization, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper presents numerical results and comparisons with other methods, which falls under the category of simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
